Text.SourceString: It's raining. The plants will be happy to get water.
Text.LocalizedString: It's raining. The plants will be happy to get water.

Text.SourceString: I like the sound of rain. It's calming.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the sound of rain. It's calming.

Text.SourceString: When it rains, everything feels fresh and new.
Text.LocalizedString: When it rains, everything feels fresh and new.

Text.SourceString: Storms are powerful. It's best to stay safe inside.
Text.LocalizedString: Storms are powerful. It's best to stay safe inside.

Text.SourceString: I watch the lightning and listen to the thunder. It's exciting but a little scary.
Text.LocalizedString: I watch the lightning and listen to the thunder. It's exciting but a little scary.

Text.SourceString: After a big storm, the world looks different.
Text.LocalizedString: After a big storm, the world looks different.

Text.SourceString: Snow falling is beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow falling is beautiful.

Text.SourceString: Everything is quiet when it snows. It's peaceful.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything is quiet when it snows. It's peaceful.

Text.SourceString: Snow is fun but cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow is fun but cold.

Text.SourceString: Snow season is here and everything slows down. It's a time for rest.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow season is here and everything slows down. It's a time for rest.

Text.SourceString: Sprouting season is here. Everything starts to grow again. It's time to eat.
Text.LocalizedString: Sprouting season is here. Everything starts to grow again. It's time to eat.

Text.SourceString: I like sprouting season.
Text.LocalizedString: I like sprouting season.

Text.SourceString: This season is busy for planting so Giants can eat.
Text.LocalizedString: This season is busy for planting so Giants can eat.

Text.SourceString: Gardening is peaceful. I enjoy the quiet and seeing the results of my work.
Text.LocalizedString: Gardening is peaceful. I enjoy the quiet and seeing the results of my work.

Text.SourceString: Watering plants is my favorite part.
Text.LocalizedString: Watering plants is my favorite part.

Text.SourceString: Forest animals are interesting to watch. They all have different ways of living.
Text.LocalizedString: Forest animals are interesting to watch. They all have different ways of living.

Text.SourceString: I like listening to the birds.
Text.LocalizedString: I like listening to the birds.

Text.SourceString: Watching squirrels is fun. They're always busy with something.
Text.LocalizedString: Watching squirrels is fun. They're always busy with something.

Text.SourceString: The forest is full of life. Every animal has its place.
Text.LocalizedString: The forest is full of life. Every animal has its place.

Text.SourceString: Cooking is fun. I like human food.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooking is fun. I like human food.

Text.SourceString: I respect Gort for trying to make things right. It's not easy.
Text.LocalizedString: I respect Gort for trying to make things right. It's not easy.

Text.SourceString: I love Gort.
Text.LocalizedString: I love Gort.

Text.SourceString: Gort is powerful, but he's learned to be careful with his power.
Text.LocalizedString: Gort is powerful, but he's learned to be careful with his power.

Text.SourceString: Gort and I don't always agree, but I don't care. I'll always love him.
Text.LocalizedString: Gort and I don't always agree, but I don't care. I'll always love him.

Text.SourceString: I don't know how to make human food. You could teach me.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't know how to make human food. You could teach me.

Text.SourceString: You should make human food and give it to the Giants. We like it.
Text.LocalizedString: You should make human food and give it to the Giants. We like it.

Text.SourceString: Magic doesn't scare you. I've seen humans. They're easily scared.//You're special.
Text.LocalizedString: Magic doesn't scare you. I've seen humans. They're easily scared.//You're special.

Text.SourceString: You live on a large piece of land. Why so big, question?
Text.LocalizedString: You live on a large piece of land. Why so big, question?

Text.SourceString: I can hear you gardening from here. You're loud.
Text.LocalizedString: I can hear you gardening from here. You're loud.

Text.SourceString: Cows are large. If I eat a lot of grass, maybe I'll get large like them.//Giu need try that.
Text.LocalizedString: Cows are large. If I eat a lot of grass, maybe I'll get large like them.//Giu need try that.

Text.SourceString: You have cows, question? Can I come to your land and play with the cows, question?
Text.LocalizedString: You have cows, question? Can I come to your land and play with the cows, question?

Text.SourceString: I'm learning to speak to cows. It's a very hard language to understand, even harder than human language.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm learning to speak to cows. It's a very hard language to understand, even harder than human language.

Text.SourceString: Cows have large ears. It must be nice to have ears that big.
Text.LocalizedString: Cows have large ears. It must be nice to have ears that big.

Text.SourceString: The chieftain said we're born the way we are. Giu can not be cow and cow can not be Giu.
Text.LocalizedString: The chieftain said we're born the way we are. Giu can not be cow and cow can not be Giu.

Text.SourceString: Giu likes to sleep, usually when it's dark. Humans sleep too, question?
Text.LocalizedString: Giu likes to sleep, usually when it's dark. Humans sleep too, question?

Text.SourceString: You have fancy clothing. Where do you get it, question?
Text.LocalizedString: You have fancy clothing. Where do you get it, question?

Text.SourceString: Giu went to your land this morning. Got lost.
Text.LocalizedString: Giu went to your land this morning. Got lost.

Text.SourceString: You are tall. Giu is not very tall.
Text.LocalizedString: You are tall. Giu is not very tall.

Text.SourceString: I like Gong, Groo, and Grog. But I like Gort the most. Is it unfair, question?//Gort is my twin. We have the same fire.
Text.LocalizedString: I like Gong, Groo, and Grog. But I like Gort the most. Is it unfair, question?//Gort is my twin. We have the same fire.

Text.SourceString: Chieftain said no cows in the village. Afraid there's no space for them.
Text.LocalizedString: Chieftain said no cows in the village. Afraid there's no space for them.

Text.SourceString: Giu went to see the cows near your land. They are gentle beasts.
Text.LocalizedString: Giu went to see the cows near your land. They are gentle beasts.

Text.SourceString: You look like you need a lot of water to cool off. You're tall.
Text.LocalizedString: You look like you need a lot of water to cool off. You're tall.

Text.SourceString: So many colors and music in the lake festival. Humans know how to celebrate.
Text.LocalizedString: So many colors and music in the lake festival. Humans know how to celebrate.

Text.SourceString: A lot of food at the lake festival. And a large shiny cow.//Humans know how to celebrate.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of food at the lake festival. And a large shiny cow.//Humans know how to celebrate.

Text.SourceString: This little creature, a cat you call it, question? It's so soft and moves with such grace.
Text.LocalizedString: This little creature, a cat you call it, question? It's so soft and moves with such grace.

Text.SourceString: I saw a machine that drips delicious liquid in the human village.//Humans make interesting things.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a machine that drips delicious liquid in the human village.//Humans make interesting things.

Text.SourceString: Squirrels are always busy, running around. They're like you, always moving.
Text.LocalizedString: Squirrels are always busy, running around. They're like you, always moving.

Text.SourceString: You are a squirrel. Funny, I joke.
Text.LocalizedString: You are a squirrel. Funny, I joke.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Giu</> remember you. Thank you!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Giu</> remember you. Thank you!

Text.SourceString: We miss <NPCName>Gort</>, my twin. You will find <NPCName>Gort</> too?
Text.LocalizedString: We miss <NPCName>Gort</>, my twin. You will find <NPCName>Gort</> too?

Text.SourceString: What Giants do here, it is not silly tricks.//<NPCName>Giu</> connect with Universe.
Text.LocalizedString: What Giants do here, it is not silly tricks.//<NPCName>Giu</> connect with Universe.

Text.SourceString: Magic is a powerful force in the world.//<NPCName>Giu</> have to be careful weilding it.
Text.LocalizedString: Magic is a powerful force in the world.//<NPCName>Giu</> have to be careful weilding it.

Text.SourceString: Giants can do great things through magic.//A scary thought.
Text.LocalizedString: Giants can do great things through magic.//A scary thought.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Giu</> not as good as magic as <NPCName>Gort</>. Nobody was.//It was pitiful what <NPCName>Gort</> did to us...stoned his family like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Giu</> not as good as magic as <NPCName>Gort</>. Nobody was.//It was pitiful what <NPCName>Gort</> did to us...stoned his family like that.

Text.SourceString: Magic is everywhere.//You just need to open your eyes.
Text.LocalizedString: Magic is everywhere.//You just need to open your eyes.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Giu</> can't make good food like Hooman.//Why is that?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Giu</> can't make good food like Hooman.//Why is that?

Text.SourceString: Ice Season is good. Sometimes we don't need fire. Let Nature be.
Text.LocalizedString: Ice Season is good. Sometimes we don't need fire. Let Nature be.

Text.SourceString: Hooman usually rest in Ice Season.
Text.LocalizedString: Hooman usually rest in Ice Season.

Text.SourceString: Oh no, that Animal...Animal rest in Ice Seaon.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no, that Animal...Animal rest in Ice Seaon.

Text.SourceString: I can light the forest on fire, but <NPCName>Giu</> don't want to.//<NPCName>Giu</> not cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I can light the forest on fire, but <NPCName>Giu</> don't want to.//<NPCName>Giu</> not cold.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Giu</> like heat.This time when Animal sing at night.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Giu</> like heat.This time when Animal sing at night.

Text.SourceString: You remind <NPCName>Giu</> of Fish Hooman.//Only your face, that is... You have long stick-y legs, Fish Hooman have slimey tails.
Text.LocalizedString: You remind <NPCName>Giu</> of Fish Hooman.//Only your face, that is... You have long stick-y legs, Fish Hooman have slimey tails.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Giu</> need to practice!//You on the way. Goombye.
